    "## Step 2: The partitioned Parquet warehouse\n",
    "\n",
    "The engineering payoff is in the storage layer. The fetch script writes Hive-style\n",
    "month-partitioned Parquet (`year_month=YYYY-MM/`), the same pattern the\n",
    "[Data Foundation](../data-foundation/data-engineering.html) page describes, just at a\n",
    "coarser grain than production hourly data would use.\n",
    "\n",
    "::: {.callout-note}\n",
    "**On partition grain.** I deliberately partition by month, not by day, even though the\n",
    "data is daily. With 103 articles × 92 days, a per-day partition would mean ~100 rows per\n",
    "file, small enough that Parquet's per-file metadata overhead dominates the actual column\n",
    "data and the format loses to plain CSV. Month partitions land at ~3,000 rows each, which\n",
    "is enough for columnar compression to actually win. The same dataset at hourly bulk-dump\n",
    "grain (~7M rows/hour) would partition by date with ease. Pick the partition column to\n",
    "match the grain of the data, not the calendar.\n",
    ":::"
   ]
