    "## Step 4: The detection algorithm\n",
    "\n",
    "Robust statistics matter here. **Mean and standard deviation break down when outliers are\n",
    "the thing you're trying to detect.** The outlier inflates the standard deviation, which\n",
    "raises the threshold, which masks the next outlier. A classic feedback loop (there's a\n",
    "chart of this failure further down).\n",
    "\n",
    "The fix is **median + MAD (median absolute deviation)**. The median ignores extreme\n",
    "values, and MAD scaled by 1.4826 is a consistent estimator of the standard deviation\n",
    "under normality, so the z-scores stay interpretable.\n",
    "\n",
    "Detection runs in two tiers, because real spikes come in two shapes:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Persistent tier:** robust z > 5 for at least 2 consecutive days. Catches sustained\n",
    "  events while filtering one-day noise. This is the tier that earns the ×2 Bitcoin\n",
    "  slow burn.\n",
    "- **Extreme tier:** robust z > 12 on any single day. Exists because a genuinely large\n",
    "  one-day event (our planted ×5 Elon Musk day lands around z ≈ 47) should not be thrown\n",
    "  away just because it didn't persist."
   ]
  },
